    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Finch</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the pleasure to receive the following
                    telegram on the 11th instant, in the evening, from the Hon. José Decoud,
                    minister for foreign affairs for the Republic of Paraguay: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asuncion</hi>, <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1898.</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">To <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Finch</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister, Montevideo:</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>Yesterday I had the honor to receive your excellency’s note, dated April
                            26 ultimo, communicating that a state of war exists between the United
                            States and Spain; and <pb facs="0989" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/> I hasten
                            to make known to your excellency, in accordance with the wishes and
                            instructions of the President of the Republic, that the Government of
                            Paraguay, faithful to its international duties, will maintain the
                            strictest neutrality during the said conflict.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">José Decoud.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Finch.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
